headline: Your Company Probably Doesn’t Need Its Own L2
summary: According to EY’s Global Blockchain Leader Paul Brody, only companies that can aggregate significant transaction volume into the network, and whose customers can't make their own direct connection to Ethereum, would benefit from creating their own layer 2.

headline: How the Narrative for Robinhood Is Shifting Amid Innovation Expansion and Analyst Optimism
summary: Robinhood Markets has seen its consensus analyst price target move only slightly higher, from $113.09 to $114.99, following the latest update. Despite this marginal change, analysts point to the company's rapid product innovation, global expansion, and strong financial performance as key reasons behind continued optimism. headline: Foundations Shored Up Endowments in 2024. Nonprofits Need the Funding.
summary: Last year’s average returns of private and community foundations lagged slightly behind 2023, yet still showed double-digit gains. But they still found themselves under pressure from strapped nonprofits.
